    "body": "### Problem\n\nTreesitter syntax highlighting started to fail (see video) for me after commit: [5edbabdbec](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/5edbabdbec0ac3fba33be8afc008845130158583)\n\nI was able to replicate the issue by increasing my terminal font size.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/36cdb190-8ecb-47df-9225-c6322bd535fb\n\nCommit that causes the issue: [5edbabdbec](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/5edbabdbec0ac3fba33be8afc008845130158583)\n\nTested on `st`, `tmux` and `ghostty` terminals. It doesn't seems to happen on `konsole` or `kitty`.\n\n---\n\n> repro.html\n\n[pastebin repro.html](https://pastebin.com/BMm34jjz)\n\n> minimal.lua\n\n```lua\nlocal repro_dir = vim.fs.joinpath(vim.uv.cwd(), \".repro\")\nvim.env.XDG_CONFIG_HOME = repro_dir .. \"/config\"\nvim.env.XDG_DATA_HOME = repro_dir .. \"/share\"\nvim.env.XDG_STATE_HOME = repro_dir .. \"/state\"\nvim.env.XDG_CACHE_HOME = repro_dir .. \"/cache\"\n\nvim.opt.packpath:prepend(repro_dir .. \"/share/nvim/site\")\n\nvim.pack.add({\n  {\n    src = \"https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter\",\n    version = \"main\",\n  },\n})\n\nvim.cmd.syntax(\"off\")\nvim.o.swapfile = false\nvim.go.backup = false\n\n--- these options cause the problem\nvim.wo.number = true\nvim.wo.signcolumn = \"auto:2-4\"\nvim.wo.wrap = false\nvim.wo.foldcolumn = \"1\"\nvim.go.showtabline = 2\n\nrequire(\"nvim-treesitter\").setup({\n  install_dir = repro_dir .. \"share/nvim/site/\",\n})\n\nrequire(\"nvim-treesitter\").install(\"html\")\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", {\n  pattern = \"html\",\n  callback = function()\n    vim.treesitter.start()\n  end,\n})\n```\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. copy minimal.lua and repro.html on the same directory\n2. open `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n3. open `:e repro.html`\n4. go to line 1130 (is where the issue happens)\n5. Start increasing your terminal font size until you see the same issue as in the video.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSyntax highlighting should not fail\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1147+g069be91106-dirty\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narch\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst latest, ghostty latest, tmux latest\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
